/-! ## §8 — THE LAST-ROW BINDING FIX (the `AdjacencyMembershipEmit.adjLastOrderFix` counterpart).

`noteSpendConstraints` lowers C1 (`is_merkle` boolean), C2-final (`COMMITMENT == COMMITMENT_FULL`), the
three C2-links (value / value_hi / asset ↔ commitment limb), and C5 (position validity) as
`.base (.gate …)` — TRANSITION constraints, VACUOUS on the last row (`holdsVm … isLast=true (.gate _)
= True`, `EffectVmEmit.lean:465`). But the DEPLOYED DSL AIR lowers every one of those local kinds as an
EVERY-ROW `assert_zero` (`Binary`/`Equality`/`Polynomial`/`Gated`/`InvertedGated` → `assert_zero`,
`circuit/src/dsl/dsl_p3_air.rs:33-38`; only `Transition` is `when_transition()`). So the emitted IR-v2
descriptor is STRICTLY WEAKER than the deployed circuit on the last row: on a HEIGHT-1 trace (row 0 IS
the last row, `is_merkle = 0`) the `COMMITMENT` column (col 5) is FREE — decoupled from the full-width
commitment binding (col 54) that the nullifier chain (C3/C4) rides — a genuine forge
(`NoteSpendingLeafRung2.forgeTrace_satisfied2` accepts it under this descriptor).

`noteSpendLastRowFix` re-lowers exactly those six every-row bodies as `.base (.boundary VmRow.last …)`
(fires on the last row too — `holdsVm … isLast=true (.boundary .last b) = (b.eval = 0)`). Composed with
the transition `.gate`s (rows `0..n-2`), each body now vanishes on EVERY row — matching the deployed
`assert_zero`. This is the note-spend twin of `AdjacencyMembershipEmit.adjLastOrderFix`. The C7
`.windowGate` stays `on_transition` (a cross-row copy; the terminal `CURRENT` is pinned DIRECTLY by the
last-row `piBinding` col0==pi1 — exactly the deployed `Transition` → `when_transition()` shape), and the
12 chip lookups already fire on every row (multiset semantics, no transition zerofier). -/

/-- **The last-row binding fix** — the six every-row local-gate bodies (C1 / C2-final / C2-link×3 / C5)
re-lowered as `VmRow.last` boundary constraints, covering the last row the transition `.gate`s make
vacuous. This is what closes the height-1 `COMMITMENT`-freedom forge. -/
def noteSpendLastRowFix : List VmConstraint2 :=
  [ .base (.boundary VmRow.last (binaryGate IS_MERKLE))       -- C1  is_merkle boolean
  , .base (.boundary VmRow.last (invEqGate IS_MERKLE 5 54))   -- C2-final COMMITMENT == COMMITMENT_FULL
  , .base (.boundary VmRow.last (invEqGate IS_MERKLE 1 28))   -- C2-link value == VALUE_LO
  , .base (.boundary VmRow.last (invEqGate IS_MERKLE 19 29))  -- C2-link value_hi == VALUE_HI limb
  , .base (.boundary VmRow.last (invEqGate IS_MERKLE 2 30))   -- C2-link asset == ASSET_LO
  , .base (.boundary VmRow.last posGate) ]                    -- C5  position validity

/-- **`noteSpendLeafDescFixed`** — `noteSpendLeafDesc` with the last-row binding fix appended. This is
the descriptor the deployed `note_spend_to_descriptor2()` producer MUST emit to be faithful to the
deployed DSL AIR (every-row `assert_zero`). Wiring it into the byte-pinned `noteSpendLeafDesc` +
`circuit/descriptors/by-name/note-spend-leaf.json` + the Rust producer + the deployed VK is a
COORDINATED shared-file change (reported as the residual); this variant + the Rung-2 regression proof
below prove the closure is correct and ready. -/
def noteSpendLeafDescFixed : EffectVmDescriptor2 :=
  { noteSpendLeafDesc with constraints := noteSpendConstraints ++ noteSpendLastRowFix }

